<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<LP>
   HONG KONG -- The government lowered its 1990 gross
domestic product growth estimate to 2.5% from 3%, and
increased its estimate for this year's inflation rate to 9.5%
from 8.5%.
   An official said that the revisions were largely
influenced by the crisis in the Persian Gulf, but that the
weaker trends were in place even before Iraq seized Kuwait.
</LP>
