<HL>
   China Dissident Fang
   To Teach at Princeton
</HL>
<DATE>
08/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B3A
</SO>
<LP>
   PRINCETON, N.J. -- Fang Lizhi, 54-year-old Chinese
astrophysicist and exiled dissident, will join Princeton
University's astrophysics faculty next year.
   Mr. Fang -- one of China's most famous dissidents and a
leader of the democracy movement there -- is currently a
professor at Cambridge University's Institute of Astronomy, a
post he has held since he was permitted to leave the U.S.
Embassy in Beijing last month.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Fang will move to Princeton after spending one term,
starting Jan. 1, at the nearby Institute of Advanced Studies
as a visiting scholar.
