<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Everest &amp; Jennings International Ltd. reported a
second-quarter loss of $4 million, or 44 cents a share, and
said that its ability to continue domestic operations depends
on successful negotiation of a new credit agreement.
   In the year-earlier quarter, the maker of wheelchairs and
other medical equipment, posted a loss of $5.5 million, or 68
