<HL>
   Business Brief -- ASK Corp.:
   Pact Set With Union Fund
   For a $20 Million Infusion
</HL>
<DATE>
08/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6C
</SO>
<CO>
   ASKC LABOR
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   ASK Corp. of Waco, Texas, said it entered into a letter of
understanding with the Sheet Metal Workers' National Pension
Fund, regarding the previously announced plan of the fund and
another institution to infuse $20 million of debt and equity
into the maker of natural gas heating and airconditioning
systems.
   ASK said the letter sets out the main elements of a
proposed definitive agreement, and establishes projected time
frames for completion of due diligience and closing of the
transaction, subject to approval by the boards of the three
parties involved.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said it plans to use the $20 million to
acquire "certain technology and equipment," but ASK President
Brian D. Pardo declined to discuss details of the proposed
acquisitions or identify the third party involved in the
negotiations.
</TEXT>
